  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We propose an extension of the well-known formalism for gauge-invariant scalar metric fluctuations, to study the spectrums for both, the inflaton and gauge invariant (scalar) metric fluctuations in the framework of a single field inflationary model where the quasi-exponential expansion is driven by an inflation which is minimally coupled to gravity. We conclude that back reaction effects due to metric fluctuations on cosmological scales should be negligible at the end of inflation. The proposal is valid also for fluctuations with large amplitude.</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">arXiv</subfield>
